<br>
I stood silently in the center of the main room for a while, gathering my thoughts, the others going to find places to sit or lay down and relaxe after the long walk.  Finally, when the shuffling of feet and rubbing of moving bodies ended, I turned and looked around at the ragtag group and sighed heavly.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  We're doomed...  We are f*cking doomed...  We're going to die, and I'll finally get to see Achi again..</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a slight smile crossed my lips at that thought, then faded nearly instantly as I looked to Tani once more.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  By the gods, where ever the hell you may be hiding your bleach white *sses right now, if any of us are going to live, Tani will.  Even is I have to knock her out myself and translocate her back to Greater Faydark, she's going to make it..</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Another sigh escaped my lips.<br>
<br>
&quot;Okay..so what do we do Undeen?&quot; Derren was the first to speak.<br>
<br>
The words hit me like the cold slap of water against my face.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  They look to me like a leader.  They all do.  Even Brutus.  What am I going to tell them?  That they should all run to their perspective corners and hide, and save themselves what is likely to be a very painful, and slow death?  Or lie to them and try and convince them to fight?  Truth...  They'll appreciate the warning in the end.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
a soft swollow, a breath, and finally words slipped from tongue out onto the wind to be heard.  My voice didn't waver.  Brownie point for me.  &quot;Truthfully, it looks like we are going to hold ground at Old Torsis.  the Iksar are marching this way, they've been hearding the battle drums more recently.&quot;<br>
<br>
Derren seemed a little eager.  And even that little eagerness was too much.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Ugh....  I think I'm going to be sick when I see them all go pale after this...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Truthfully, I think the Iksar are going to march on Old Torsis.  They'll take heavy hits in the Jungle, but they will make it.  And I think we will all likely die here, a slow, horrible death.  But then, I tend to be very pesemistic when it comes to if I'll servive a fight or not.  Remember.  It only takes one arrow to kill you, no matter how good you are.&quot;  All their faces dropped and they all god a pale look.  The Erudite looked horrible.  Don't think he had thought he would die when he woke up this morning.  At least I had had that warning from the beginning.  And ya, the looks made me want to be sick right there.  Always did.<br>
<br>
&quot;Right now, I'm willing to offer you a choice.  Stand and fight with myself, and the denizens of Old Torsis, or I can translocate out any of you who wish freedom.  I don't blame you, or claim cowardous, any who wish to leave.  I myself would leave, had I not a deathwish.&quot;  It sounded so silly I almost wanted to smile.  Almost.  Ya, to be with Achi again, I really did have a death wish.  She would be worth that couple minutes of pain.<br>
<br>
&quot;So.  Who stays and stares death in the faces with me, and who heads home to hug your families, and be thankful you made the decision that lets you remain with them?&quot;<br>
<br>
