se people, maybe they all could be friends with Him. Then there wouldn't be any more fighting back home. Then she wouldn't have to hide in the trees or slip past the gaurds. She could be happy like she wanted, and he would be happy as well. That's all she wanted. She wanted Him to be happy. This would make Him happy. It had to. He would see she was no longer a child. He would see. With a reassuring nod and a stern face, she looks up at Undeen. <br>
<br>
&quot;I will stay. I want to help.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her eyes burned with determination as she stared up at the shadow elf. What... What if he didn't let her stay? Wouldn't he let her help? It was her decision. Her decision. Not his. With her little hands balled up in fists at her sides, she looks again from person to person. Why was it, that they all looked so... sad?<br>
