<br>
The barbarian thrust his spear into the throat of a wizard behind him; she'd not seen the massive man, somehow, and was busy letting her heart magic flow in a steady stream, attempting to slice the heads clean off rows of undead. The more agilitous(sp?) ones ducked, and others kept walking without heads. Either way, her chest burst outwards in a torrent of flames as her life force was expended. Brutus smiled, and realized that the gash on his right arm had already healed. He let his mind go once more, and slipped into clairvoyant perception for a single instant;<br>
<br>
